<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jordaens, Goergen &amp; De Meyer" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Mesembrius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mesembrius arcuatus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arcuatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Mesembrius arcuatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Latin) means bent like a bow and was chosen with reference to the strongly curved metatibia. It is to be treated as an adjective (nominative singular masculine).
</paragraph>
